# Wordly Dictionary SPA

## What is this project?
This is my Wordly Dictionary project. I built this Single Page Application (SPA) to help people find word meanings, synonyms, and audio pronunciations quickly and easily.

## What I Used
* **HTML5**: I used this to create the structure of the site, like the search bar, the result headers, and the audio player.
* **CSS3**: I used CSS to style the app. I made sure to use `max-width` and `margin: 0 auto` so that the app stays centered in the middle of the screen on laptops.
* **JavaScript**: This is the most important part. I used JavaScript to "fetch" data from the Free Dictionary API and update the page dynamically without the user having to refresh.

## How it Works
When you type a word and hit the "Search" button:
1. My JavaScript code grabs the word you typed from the input box.
2. It sends that word to an external Dictionary API.
3. If the word is found, the code swaps the "Result Title" with your word and fills in the definition and synonyms.
4. If there is a recording available, the audio player will appear so you can hear the word.
5. If the word doesn't exist, I added "Error Handling" so the app shows a friendly message saying the word wasn't found.

## How to Run it
To see the app in action:
1. Open my `index.html` file in any web browser.
2. Type a common word like "Library" or "Code."
3. Click "Search" and the results will appear instantly!

## Reflections
The trickiest part for me was making sure the API URL was written correctly using backticks so the search variable would work. I also learned a lot about how to use the browser console to find errors when my code wasn't working at first.